definition.value: An abnormal lesion or swelling seen on gallbladder imaging.

label.value: Abnormal muscle tissue enzyme activity or level

definition.value: Any deviation from the normal activity or histological staining of an enzyme in muscle tissue, usually measured in a muscle biopsy specimen.
An elevation in the concentration of interferon alpha measured in the blood circulation.
A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the liver.
The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that react positively with acid fuchsin.
Deterioration of the cells of the myenteric plexus (also known as the Auerbach plexus) located between the layers of the muscular propria of the esophagus.
Presence of an elevated number of eosinophils in a lymph node (usually as demonstrated by lymph node biopsy).
Presence of trypomastigote parasites in the blood stream. This finding can be demonstrated by the identification of trypomastigote parasites on peripheral blood smear.

label.value: Abnormal enzyme activity in muscle tissue

definition.value: Deviation from the normal activity of an enzyme in muscle tissue.

label.value: Reduced fibroblast type III procollagen synthesis

definition.value: Diminished production of type III procollagen by cultured skin fibroblasts.
Elevated amount of glycogen in the myocardium.
Reduced activity of the enzyme delta-aminolevulinate dehydratase. The enzyme is active in erythrocytes.

label.value: Elevated circulating pancreatic secretory trypsin inhibitor activity

definition.value: Deposition of calcium in meconium present in the internal cavity of the fetal bowel. This manifestation may be the result of any distal intestinal obstruction.
A developmental defect characterized by underdevelopment of the portal vein.
Reduced number of observable peroxisomes per cell. This feature can be observed by immunohistochemical staining of cultured cells (such as fibroblasts) or by electronmicroscopy.
Reduced activity of the enzyme sulfide:quinone oxidoreductase, which typically is measured in a biopsy specimen from liver or muscle.

label.value: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of the bladder

definition.value: A malginant rhabdoid tumor (MRT) originating in the liver. MRT are best characterized by the presence of round or polygonal cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm, typical eosinophilic perinuclear inclusions, vesicular nuclei and prominent nucleoli. Immunohistochemical expression of vimentin and epithelial markers and lack of staining for S-100, myoglobin and desmin are commonly found, but are non-specific.
A teratoma located in the neck.
A teratoma located in a kidney.
